1
00:00:16,333 --> 00:00:21,500
but the most useful thing we can craft with some more steel is a charcoal pile igniter

2
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:24,200
to use it, we first have to dig a huge hole

3
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:25,633
with some bricks on the bottom

4
00:00:25,833 --> 00:00:27,633
we fill that hole with logs

5
00:00:27,766 --> 00:00:30,066
and after covering all of the wood with dirt

6
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:32,633
we put an new machinery on top of it

7
00:00:32,833 --> 00:00:35,766
and it was then that something weird happened

8
00:00:35,766 --> 00:00:37,900
a wild giant brick (?) appeared

9
00:00:37,900 --> 00:00:40,000
maybe we have touched too much grass

10
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:43,300
and this is the quest book telling us to go touch bricks

11
00:00:43,300 --> 00:00:47,033
and the first thing we can do of those bronze plated bricks

12
00:00:47,033 --> 00:00:49,333
is a multiblock steam alloy smelter

13
00:00:49,666 --> 00:00:51,900
since that thing will eat a lot of steam

14
00:00:51,966 --> 00:00:56,966
we start by using it to produce a new alloy we only dreamed of, stronze

15
00:00:57,533 --> 00:00:59,733
sturdy as steel and valuable as bronze

16
00:01:00,333 --> 00:01:04,166
this materials is indeed great both for pipes and for tools

17
00:01:04,766 --> 00:01:09,533
we can also use the extra space in our new machine to alloy some clay compound

18
00:01:10,066 --> 00:01:14,800
that is the only material enough lightweight and sturdy to make our new hydraulic parts

19
00:01:16,366 --> 00:01:19,466
but of course the first thing we have to do

20
00:01:19,466 --> 00:01:23,733
is break many tools in order to work the dozens of stacks of metal ingots

21
00:01:23,733 --> 00:01:26,000
required to make some hydraulic motors

22
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:28,833
with those new hydraulic parts

23
00:01:28,833 --> 00:01:30,766
we can craft to Carpenter

24
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:33,900
which will allow us to do more advanced stuff with wood

25
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:35,400
such as plating it

26
00:01:35,933 --> 00:01:37,166
and with plated wood

27
00:01:37,300 --> 00:01:38,666
we can make a woodcutter

28
00:01:38,933 --> 00:01:41,166
and that machine doesn't just cut wood

29
00:01:41,366 --> 00:01:44,500
it also grows it with the power of steam

30
00:01:44,966 --> 00:01:45,966
after building it

31
00:01:45,966 --> 00:01:48,266
we set it up to cultivate cactus

32
00:01:48,300 --> 00:01:51,866
which we can use to feed our new maximum sized boiler

33
00:01:52,100 --> 00:01:53,566
with all of that steam

34
00:01:53,700 --> 00:01:55,933
we can now power some bigger machinery

35
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:58,733
the first one is going to be the Steam Conformer

36
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:01,733
which is an improved version of the Forge Hammer

37
00:02:01,733 --> 00:02:04,533
which allow for hammering stuff into of various shapes

38
00:02:04,533 --> 00:02:09,066
making it more versatile than a forge hammer but not as efficient as an extruder

39
00:02:09,300 --> 00:02:11,200
next we build a steam blender

40
00:02:11,466 --> 00:02:16,766
that mixer will allow us to mix the malleability of bronze with the sturdiness of steel

41
00:02:16,766 --> 00:02:17,633
making breel

42
00:02:17,633 --> 00:02:20,500
which must not be confused with stronze

43
00:02:20,966 --> 00:02:23,266
and by using both of those materials

44
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:25,466
we can build a better blast furnace

45
00:02:25,700 --> 00:02:28,300
but this one works in a slight different way

46
00:02:28,566 --> 00:02:30,166
after feeding it materials

47
00:02:30,366 --> 00:02:32,500
it will turn on but it won't work

48
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:36,366
that is because it will turn steam input into time progress

49
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,833
so we add a steam input pipe

50
00:02:38,833 --> 00:02:44,066
and now we see how nicely it works with just a small steel pipe worth of steam

51
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:48,700
it works so nicely that it quickly used up all of our carbon fuel

52
00:02:49,100 --> 00:02:53,666
to fix that, we rooted some cactus into the new infernal coke oven

53
00:02:53,666 --> 00:02:56,033
this will make cactus charcoal

54
00:02:56,033 --> 00:03:00,900
which we then pass again inside another infernal coke oven to make cactus coke

55
00:03:00,900 --> 00:03:03,666
which we can now feed to our blast furnace

56
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:06,700
those two can also keep up with our boiler

57
00:03:06,733 --> 00:03:09,566
and they didn't even reach their final speed yet

58
00:03:09,966 --> 00:03:12,600
but if we want to make steel even faster

59
00:03:12,733 --> 00:03:15,133
we can use a hotter kind of steam

60
00:03:15,866 --> 00:03:19,566
we can achieve that by fusing normal steam with creosote oil

61
00:03:19,733 --> 00:03:21,466
making superheated steam

62
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:24,300
we pump that into our blast furnace

63
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:26,466
and now we can make instant steel

64
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:30,566
with all of that steel we can build an extractinator

65
00:03:30,933 --> 00:03:34,466
then we also built some extra machines to support it

66
00:03:35,066 --> 00:03:37,033
it all starts from a steam cobbler

67
00:03:37,033 --> 00:03:40,966
which will make cobblestone from lava water interaction

68
00:03:40,966 --> 00:03:44,266
cobblestone is then smashed down into gravel

69
00:03:44,266 --> 00:03:50,000
next, it is mixed to water, forming a sluice which is finally feed to our extractinator

70
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:53,100
here, with the power of super heated steam

71
00:03:53,133 --> 00:03:57,433
we can extract all sorts of goodies out of watered stone

72
00:03:57,433 --> 00:04:01,966
next, we filter those goodies and work the best stuff into ingots

73
00:04:01,966 --> 00:04:04,466
and thus, with a couple more of machines

74
00:04:04,566 --> 00:04:07,966
we have an unlimited source of bronze, iron and steel

75
00:04:09,133 --> 00:04:12,300
which we bring right into our base

76
00:04:12,300 --> 00:04:14,666
however, as you'd probably expect

77
00:04:14,766 --> 00:04:16,766
we quickly run out of steam

78
00:04:18,133 --> 00:04:22,066
luckily, by extracting (?) obsidian sluice we can obtain silver

79
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:25,300
and I think we all know where this is going

80
00:04:26,066 --> 00:04:28,533
into a new mega pressure solar boiler

81
00:04:29,166 --> 00:04:30,100
as you can see

82
00:04:30,133 --> 00:04:34,166
it is happily boiling 100,000 liters of steam per second

83
00:04:34,933 --> 00:04:36,200
with all of that steam

84
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:39,333
we can now work on crafting a steam manufacturer

85
00:04:39,466 --> 00:04:42,666
that took quite a lot of resources and many crafting steps

86
00:04:42,966 --> 00:04:44,800
but we managed to complete it

87
00:04:45,133 --> 00:04:47,900
since once again we tried to optimize space

88
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:51,800
we can admire it in all of its glory from the NEI preview

89
00:04:52,066 --> 00:04:56,133
the first usage we have for this machine is crafting steel turbines

90
00:04:56,566 --> 00:05:00,133
with those we can upgrade our pumps to fluid regulators

91
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:03,766
which will allow us to control the flow of a jet of steam in it

92
00:05:03,766 --> 00:05:06,733
thus allowing us to pipelessly connect our machines

93
00:05:07,466 --> 00:05:11,800
and this will also allow us to use the whole universe as our steam tank

94
00:05:11,966 --> 00:05:15,400
giving us all the room for buffering energy we could possibly need

95
00:05:15,900 --> 00:05:19,466
now that we have upgraded our main machines with that new solution

96
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:23,566
we can also start looking for an even more fused kind of steam

97
00:05:23,866 --> 00:05:25,266
supercritical steam

98
00:05:25,466 --> 00:05:31,166
the easiest way to obtain it would be to add more creosote into our already superheated steam

99
00:05:31,466 --> 00:05:34,366
a cheaper way is to boil water using lava

100
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:37,400
but that requires a compact hyper pressure reactor

101
00:05:37,533 --> 00:05:39,566
which isn't too easy to craft

102
00:05:39,933 --> 00:05:45,966
the only option left is to offer our compressed cactus coke to the Cactai gods in the Cactai pantheon

103
00:05:46,266 --> 00:05:49,466
so we collect the leftover cactus we have been stocking

104
00:05:49,766 --> 00:05:51,533
compress those a couple of times

105
00:05:51,933 --> 00:05:57,200
and then bring that expensive block of super compressed cactus to the new shrine we just built

106
00:05:57,566 --> 00:06:01,933
now the cacti deities will reward us with a lot of supercritical steam

107
00:06:02,266 --> 00:06:03,066
with that acquired

108
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:05,133
we can move on to the next task

109
00:06:05,533 --> 00:06:06,733
making a new machine

110
00:06:06,966 --> 00:06:10,800
and this one doesn't really look like something we can craft by hand

111
00:06:11,266 --> 00:06:14,266
so we start working on making more stuff passively

112
00:06:14,700 --> 00:06:19,133
so, after making some more mess to passively produce all the basic materials

113
00:06:19,366 --> 00:06:22,800
we make some more mess to passively make all kinds of plates

114
00:06:23,466 --> 00:06:25,733
and it was then that we run into an issue

115
00:06:25,766 --> 00:06:29,800
if we don't want to automate to crafting table with a good stock of tools

116
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,666
we need a couple of assemblers

117
00:06:31,866 --> 00:06:33,900
and those are annoying and expensive

118
00:06:34,066 --> 00:06:36,600
but since there is no other reliable way

119
00:06:36,666 --> 00:06:39,900
we start mass producing every kind of part we can

120
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:43,300
then, after manually crafting our first assembler

121
00:06:43,333 --> 00:06:49,266
we set up some hydraulic regulators to keep it stocked with the materials needed for our super compressor

122
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:50,866
and after enough time

123
00:06:50,933 --> 00:06:52,966
we manage to get everything we needed

124
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:55,333
we fill our inventory with that stuff

125
00:06:55,333 --> 00:06:57,866
and we proceed into building the new machine 

126
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:02,000
and after realizing our inventory is small and we do not like walking

127
00:07:02,366 --> 00:07:04,200
we take the whole drawer with us

128
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:06,666
and after completing the main structure

129
00:07:06,933 --> 00:07:09,700
adding buses, hatches and pipeless power

130
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:12,866
we turn it on to compress steam into solid form

131
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:20,200
this new material will allow us to craft the most advanced technology we could only dream of in gaseous steam age

132
00:07:20,733 --> 00:07:21,533
for example

133
00:07:21,700 --> 00:07:26,900
we can make screws so lightweight that will be able to lift up not only a couple of gold rings

134
00:07:27,100 --> 00:07:29,700
but also the people attached to those rings

135
00:07:30,266 --> 00:07:33,566
now we can also access the Jetstream wireless hatches

136
00:07:33,566 --> 00:07:35,800
and build some new giant mega blocks

137
00:07:36,133 --> 00:07:41,600
but what we really are after is the more advanced hydraulic Jetstream Enchanted technology

138
00:07:42,333 --> 00:07:46,100
however, those parts require some peculiar gems and rubber

139
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:50,133
so we quickly grab the material to craft some more automation

140
00:07:50,133 --> 00:07:53,466
and automate the passive production for those things too

141
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:56,366
and after building some more spaghetti automation

142
00:07:56,666 --> 00:07:58,800
we managed to obtain our gems

143
00:07:59,133 --> 00:08:00,133
as for the rubber

144
00:08:00,133 --> 00:08:04,400
we automated it all the way up to passive fluid regulators

145
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:08,666
with that, we can easily craft some of the advanced hydraulics parts

146
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:11,400
but before using those

147
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:16,300
we shall pay tribute of a quintuple compressed cactus coke to the cacti deities

148
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:19,600
so that the supercritical steam charm will light our path

149
00:08:20,133 --> 00:08:25,500
and the next thing on our path is the infinite creation given by the perfect steam progenitor

150
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:28,933
at first that looks like a challenging thing to build

151
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:32,400
but thanks to our out of control passive restocking

152
00:08:32,566 --> 00:08:35,566
we already have most of the parts required ready

153
00:08:35,766 --> 00:08:38,666
and after crafting a bunch of extra parts

154
00:08:39,133 --> 00:08:42,133
we are finally ready to assemble the machine of our dreams

155
00:08:42,333 --> 00:08:43,366
and there it is

156
00:08:43,466 --> 00:08:44,566
in all of its glory

157
00:08:44,966 --> 00:08:48,800
but that was just one more step towards our final destination

158
00:08:49,166 --> 00:08:53,266
and crafting the ultimate machine requires quite a bunch of materials

159
00:08:53,533 --> 00:08:55,133
without getting too scared

160
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:58,766
we start working towards a bigger ore processing plant

161
00:08:58,933 --> 00:09:01,966
and while all of that stuff is being passively crafted

162
00:09:02,100 --> 00:09:06,900
we can work on something powerful enough to keep up with the demands of our ultimate construction

163
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:09,000
a steampunk Schrodinger's cat

164
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:14,100
that will act both as a spinning device and a multi dimensional linking device at once

165
00:09:14,366 --> 00:09:17,566
and while crafting it took almost no time at all

166
00:09:17,866 --> 00:09:22,433
finding its favorite food, anti money, took basically forever

167
00:09:22,433 --> 00:09:26,900
next, after spending a lot of time time alternating between idling and looking around

168
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:30,466
we managed to craft the last part of the machine of our dreams

169
00:09:30,866 --> 00:09:36,000
and with that, we have completed our steam tier into dimensional teleportation device

170
00:09:36,533 --> 00:09:43,000
but the real reward here is the alien technology that will allow us to dig caves way faster than we could ever imagine

171
00:00:16,333 --> 00:00:21,500
能用更多钢做出来的好东西，就是木炭堆点火器

172
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:24,200
要用它，首先得挖一个大坑

173
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:25,633
坑底垫上一些砖块

174
00:00:25,833 --> 00:00:27,633
然后把原木塞满这个坑

175
00:00:27,766 --> 00:00:30,066
再用泥土把原木全部盖住之后

176
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:32,633
我们把新机器放在最上面

177
00:00:32,833 --> 00:00:35,766
就在那时，怪事发生了

178
00:00:35,766 --> 00:00:37,900
一棵野生的（砖树？）出现了

179
00:00:37,900 --> 00:00:40,000
也许是因为我们摸太多的草了

180
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:43,300
这是任务书在叫我们去摸砖头

181
00:00:43,300 --> 00:00:47,033
而这批青铜镀层砖能做的第一件东西

182
00:00:47,033 --> 00:00:49,333
就是多方块蒸汽合金冶炼炉

183
00:00:49,666 --> 00:00:51,900
因为这玩意儿特别吃蒸汽

184
00:00:51,966 --> 00:00:56,966
我们先用它来生产一种梦寐以求的新合金：stronze（无官方译名）

185
00:00:57,533 --> 00:00:59,733
像钢一样结实，像青铜一样值钱

186
00:01:00,333 --> 00:01:04,166
这种材料做管道和工具都非常好用

187
00:01:04,766 --> 00:01:09,533
我们还可以利用新机器里多出来的空间，顺便合成一些黏土化合物

188
00:01:10,066 --> 00:01:14,800
这是唯一一种又轻又结实、足以制作新液压部件的材料

189
00:01:16,366 --> 00:01:19,466
但当然，首先要做的是

190
00:01:19,466 --> 00:01:23,733
先折断一堆工具，去处理几十组金属锭

191
00:01:23,733 --> 00:01:26,000
这些都是做液压马达需要的材料

192
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:28,833
有了这些新的液压部件

193
00:01:28,833 --> 00:01:30,766
我们就能做出木工机

194
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:33,900
它能让我们对木材进行更高级的加工

195
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:35,400
比如给木头加覆层

196
00:01:35,933 --> 00:01:37,166
而有了覆层木材

197
00:01:37,300 --> 00:01:38,666
我们就能造出伐木机

198
00:01:38,933 --> 00:01:41,166
这台机器不只是砍树

199
00:01:41,366 --> 00:01:44,500
它还能靠蒸汽之力把树种出来

200
00:01:44,966 --> 00:01:45,966
造好之后

201
00:01:45,966 --> 00:01:48,266
我们把它设置成种仙人掌

202
00:01:48,300 --> 00:01:51,866
用来给我们新建的最大号锅炉供燃料

203
00:01:52,100 --> 00:01:53,566
有了这么多蒸汽

204
00:01:53,700 --> 00:01:55,933
我们现在就能驱动更大的机器了

205
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:58,733
第一台是蒸汽成型机

206
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:01,733
它是锻造锤的改进版

207
00:02:01,733 --> 00:02:04,533
可以把材料锤成各种形状

208
00:02:04,533 --> 00:02:09,066
比锻造锤更通用，但效率又不如挤压机

209
00:02:09,300 --> 00:02:11,200
接着我们造了一台蒸汽搅拌机

210
00:02:11,466 --> 00:02:16,766
这台搅拌机能把青铜的延展性和钢的坚固性混在一起

211
00:02:16,766 --> 00:02:17,633
做出 breel

212
00:02:17,633 --> 00:02:20,500
可别把它和 stronze 搞混了

213
00:02:20,966 --> 00:02:23,266
有了这两种材料

214
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:25,466
我们就能造出更好的高炉

215
00:02:25,700 --> 00:02:28,300
不过这一台的工作方式略有不同

216
00:02:28,566 --> 00:02:30,166
喂入材料后

217
00:02:30,366 --> 00:02:32,500
它会启动，但并不会立刻工作

218
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:36,366
因为它会把蒸汽输入转换成时间进度

219
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,833
所以我们接上了一根蒸汽输入管

220
00:02:38,833 --> 00:02:44,066
现在就能看到，只靠一根小钢管级别的蒸汽，它也能运转得很好

221
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:48,700
它效率好到很快就把我们的碳燃料全吃光了

222
00:02:49,100 --> 00:02:53,666
为了解决这个问题，我们把一些仙人掌扔进新的地狱焦炉

223
00:02:53,666 --> 00:02:56,033
先烧成仙人掌木炭

224
00:02:56,033 --> 00:03:00,900
再送进另一台地狱焦炉里继续烧成仙人掌焦炭

225
00:03:00,900 --> 00:03:03,666
现在就能拿去喂高炉了

226
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:06,700
这两台机器也能跟上锅炉的消耗

227
00:03:06,733 --> 00:03:09,566
而且它们甚至还没跑到最终速度

228
00:03:09,966 --> 00:03:12,600
但如果想让炼钢更快

229
00:03:12,733 --> 00:03:15,133
我们还可以用更热的蒸汽

230
00:03:15,866 --> 00:03:19,566
只要把普通蒸汽和杂酚油融合即可

231
00:03:19,733 --> 00:03:21,466
得到过热蒸汽

232
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:24,300
把它泵进高炉

233
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:26,466
现在我们就能瞬间炼钢

234
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:30,566
有了这些钢，我们可以造一台提取机

235
00:03:30,933 --> 00:03:34,466
然后又补了一些配套机器来支援它

236
00:03:35,066 --> 00:03:37,033
整套流程从蒸汽造石机开始

237
00:03:37,033 --> 00:03:40,966
它会利用熔岩与水的反应生成圆石

238
00:03:40,966 --> 00:03:44,266
圆石接着被粉碎成砂砾

239
00:03:44,266 --> 00:03:50,000
再和水混合成矿浆，最后送进提取机

240
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:53,100
在这里，借助过热蒸汽的力量

241
00:03:53,133 --> 00:03:57,433
我们可以从这些湿润石料里提取出各种好东西

242
00:03:57,433 --> 00:04:01,966
接着把这些产物过滤，再把最有价值的部分加工成锭

243
00:04:01,966 --> 00:04:04,466
于是，再补上几台机器后

244
00:04:04,566 --> 00:04:07,966
我们就拥有了无限的青铜、铁和钢来源

245
00:04:09,133 --> 00:04:12,300
并把它们直接送回基地

246
00:04:12,300 --> 00:04:14,666
不过，正如你可能猜到的

247
00:04:14,766 --> 00:04:16,766
我们的蒸汽很快就不够用了

248
00:04:18,133 --> 00:04:22,066
好在通过提取（？）黑曜石矿浆，我们可以拿到银

249
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:25,300
我想大家都知道接下来会发生什么

250
00:04:26,066 --> 00:04:28,533
那就是一台新的巨型高压太阳能锅炉

251
00:04:29,166 --> 00:04:30,100
如你所见

252
00:04:30,133 --> 00:04:34,166
它正在愉快地每秒烧出 100,000 升蒸汽

253
00:04:34,933 --> 00:04:36,200
有了这么多蒸汽

254
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:39,333
我们现在可以开始做蒸汽制造机了

255
00:04:39,466 --> 00:04:42,666
这需要不少资源和很多合成步骤

256
00:04:42,966 --> 00:04:44,800
但我们还是把它搞定了

257
00:04:45,133 --> 00:04:47,900
由于我们又一次试图节省空间

258
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:51,800
它的全貌就只能在 NEI 预览里欣赏了

259
00:04:52,066 --> 00:04:56,133
这台机器的第一个用途是制作钢涡轮

260
00:04:56,566 --> 00:05:00,133
有了它们，我们可以把泵升级成流体调节器

261
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:03,766
这样就能控制其中喷射蒸汽的流量

262
00:05:03,766 --> 00:05:06,733
从而让机器实现无管道连接

263
00:05:07,466 --> 00:05:11,800
这还意味着我们可以把整个宇宙当作蒸汽储罐

264
00:05:11,966 --> 00:05:15,400
给我们几乎无限的缓冲空间来储存所需能量

265
00:05:15,900 --> 00:05:19,466
现在主力机器都完成了这套升级

266
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:23,566
我们也可以开始追求更进一步融合的蒸汽

267
00:05:23,866 --> 00:05:25,266
也就是超临界蒸汽

268
00:05:25,466 --> 00:05:31,166
最简单的获取方式，是在现有过热蒸汽里继续加入更多杂酚油

269
00:05:31,466 --> 00:05:34,366
更便宜的方法是用熔岩烧水

270
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:37,400
但那需要一个紧凑型超压反应堆

271
00:05:37,533 --> 00:05:39,566
而那东西并不好做

272
00:05:39,933 --> 00:05:45,966
剩下唯一的办法，就是把压缩仙人掌焦炭献给仙人掌万神殿里的仙人掌诸神

273
00:05:46,266 --> 00:05:49,466
于是我们把之前囤着的仙人掌余料全都收集起来

274
00:05:49,766 --> 00:05:51,533
连压好几轮

275
00:05:51,933 --> 00:05:57,200
再把这块昂贵的超压缩仙人掌，搬到刚建好的新神龛里

276
00:05:57,566 --> 00:06:01,933
现在仙人掌神明就会奖励我们大量超临界蒸汽

277
00:06:02,266 --> 00:06:03,066
有了这玩意儿

278
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:05,133
我们就能推进到下一个任务

279
00:06:05,533 --> 00:06:06,733
也就是做一台新机器

280
00:06:06,966 --> 00:06:10,800
而这东西看起来可不像能手搓出来的

281
00:06:11,266 --> 00:06:14,266
所以我们开始继续扩展被动生产

282
00:06:14,700 --> 00:06:19,133
于是，在又搭出一堆混乱产线来被动生产基础材料之后

283
00:06:19,366 --> 00:06:22,800
我们又搭了一堆更乱的线来被动生产各种板材

284
00:06:23,466 --> 00:06:25,733
就在这时，我们遇到了一个问题

285
00:06:25,766 --> 00:06:29,800
如果不想给自动合成台塞上一大堆工具来自动化

286
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,666
那就得做几台组装机

287
00:06:31,866 --> 00:06:33,900
而这东西又麻烦又贵

288
00:06:34,066 --> 00:06:36,600
但既然没有别的靠谱方案

289
00:06:36,666 --> 00:06:39,900
我们只好开始量产所有能量产的部件

290
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:43,300
然后，在手工搓出第一台组装机之后

291
00:06:43,333 --> 00:06:49,266
我们布置了一些液压调节器，让它持续补充超级压缩机所需的材料

292
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:50,866
等了足够久之后

293
00:06:50,933 --> 00:06:52,966
我们总算凑齐了所有需要的东西

294
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:55,333
我们把背包装满这些材料

295
00:06:55,333 --> 00:06:57,866
然后开始搭建新机器

296
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:02,000
但很快就意识到背包太小，而且我们也不想来回跑腿

297
00:07:02,366 --> 00:07:04,200
于是直接把整柜子搬了过来

298
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:06,666
完成主体结构后

299
00:07:06,933 --> 00:07:09,700
再接上总线、仓口和无管道供能

300
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:12,866
我们启动它，把蒸汽压缩成固态

301
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:20,200
这种新材料能让我们做出在这个离谱蒸汽时代里曾经只敢想的高级技术

302
00:07:20,733 --> 00:07:21,533
比如

303
00:07:21,700 --> 00:07:26,900
我们可以做出轻到夸张的螺丝，不仅能托起几枚金戒指

304
00:07:27,100 --> 00:07:29,700
还能把挂在戒指上的人一并托起来

305
00:07:30,266 --> 00:07:33,566
现在我们也能用上 Jetstream 无线舱口

306
00:07:33,566 --> 00:07:35,800
并建造一些新的巨型多方块

307
00:07:36,133 --> 00:07:41,600
但我们真正追求的是更高级的液压 Jetstream 附魔技术

308
00:07:42,333 --> 00:07:46,100
不过这些部件需要一些特殊宝石和橡胶

309
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:50,133
所以我们赶紧去凑材料，继续加自动化

310
00:07:50,133 --> 00:07:53,466
把这些资源也做成被动产线

311
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:56,366
又堆了一堆意面式自动化之后

312
00:07:56,666 --> 00:07:58,800
我们总算拿到了宝石

313
00:07:59,133 --> 00:08:00,133
至于橡胶

314
00:08:00,133 --> 00:08:04,400
我们一路自动化到了可被动生产流体调节器的程度

315
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:08,666
这样一来，先进液压部件就能轻松做出来

316
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:11,400
但在动用这些之前

317
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:16,300
我们得向仙人掌诸神献上一块五重压缩仙人掌焦炭

318
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:19,600
让超临界蒸汽的护佑照亮前路

319
00:08:20,133 --> 00:08:25,500
而前方等待我们的，是完美蒸汽始祖赐予的无限造物

320
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:28,933
一开始这看起来很有挑战性

321
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:32,400
但多亏我们几乎失控的被动补货系统

322
00:08:32,566 --> 00:08:35,566
所需的大部分部件其实都已经备好了

323
00:08:35,766 --> 00:08:38,666
再补做一批额外零件之后

324
00:08:39,133 --> 00:08:42,133
我们终于可以组装梦想之机了

325
00:08:42,333 --> 00:08:43,366
它就在这

326
00:08:43,466 --> 00:08:44,566
光彩全开

327
00:08:44,966 --> 00:08:48,800
但这还只是通往终点的又一步

328
00:08:49,166 --> 00:08:53,266
而打造终极机器还需要海量材料

329
00:08:53,533 --> 00:08:55,133
别慌

330
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:58,766
我们先着手建设更大的矿石处理产线

331
00:08:58,933 --> 00:09:01,966
而在这些东西被动生产的同时

332
00:09:02,100 --> 00:09:06,900
我们还可以去做一件足以满足终极建造需求的强力设备

333
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:09,000
蒸汽朋克版薛定谔之猫

334
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:14,100
它会同时充当旋转装置和多维链接装置

335
00:09:14,366 --> 00:09:17,566
制作它本身几乎没花多少时间

336
00:09:17,866 --> 00:09:22,433
反而是找它最爱吃的食物 antimony，花了几乎一整辈子

337
00:09:22,433 --> 00:09:26,900
接下来，在长时间挂机和到处搜寻之间来回切换之后

338
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:30,466
我们终于做出了梦想之机的最后一个部件

339
00:09:30,866 --> 00:09:36,000
至此，我们完成了蒸汽时代的维度传送装置

340
00:09:36,533 --> 00:09:43,000
但真正的奖励，是外星科技带来的挖矿速度，快到超出想象

